					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-468742#post-1933342</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-468742/scp-1460#post-1933342</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 11 Jan 2014 11:48:55 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Altered Nova</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>81815</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm curious as to what would happen if the foundation showed his comatose body to someone affected him and explained his condition to them. Would they stop seeing his ghost? Would they deny the real body was him? Would they continue seeing his ghost despite knowing and accepting that it's some kind of illusion? (if so they could be used to perform an indirect interview with the SCP)</p> <p>Also I guess it's a good thing the guy wasn't married, his ghost interactions with his wife would get pretty weird and awkward.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
